Preheat #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g}. Quarter larger pieces. On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Arrange cut-side down then roast on the top shelf for ~{15-20%minutes}.

After ~{15%minutes}, crush each potato with the bottom of a #bowl{}. Drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice).

Return to the top shelf of the oven to cook until crispy and golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @radish{125%g}.

Pop into a bowl along with @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}, 1 tsp @sugar{1%tsp} and ¼ tsp @salt{¼%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Mix together and set aside, continuing to stir frequently.

Halve the @cabbage{1}. Cut out the tough core and thinly slice.

Toss the cabbage with half the @aioli{2%sachets}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Reserve 1 tbsp of the remaining aioli (double for 4p).

Mix what's left of the aioli with the @sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets} and @gochujang paste{1%sachet} in a bowl.

In a bowl, mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with salt and pepper.

In a separate bowl, toss the @prawns{180%g} with the reserved aioli.

Toss the prawns, one at a time, through the breadcrumbs.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Place the prawns on a lined baking tray.

Drizzle over some oil and cook in the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Place the @bao buns{6} on a #plate{} (three at a time) and microwave covered for ~{1%minute}.

Keep covered until serving.

> TIP: You can steam the bao as well. Place a large pot with 2cm of water over
> high heat. Once boiling, place a #colander{} lined with a #baking sheet{} on
> the pot. Place the bao (three at a time) on the baking sheet. Cover and
> steam for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Fill each bao with some cabbage slaw and prawns.

Drizzle with sweet chilli aioli and garnish with pickled radish.

Serve remaining slaw and smashed potatoes alongside.